The component manages a large number of state variables with individual `useState` hooks. This can become difficult to read and maintain. Consider refactoring to use a single `useReducer` hook to manage the component's state. This will group related state logic, simplify state updates, and make the component more scalable.

For example:
```typescript
const initialState = {
  devicePrice: 1500000,
  selfPurchasePrice: 1350000,
  // ... other state properties
};

function calculatorReducer(state, action) {
  switch (action.type) {
    case 'UPDATE_FIELD':
      return { ...state, [action.field]: action.value };
    // ... other actions
    default:
      throw new Error();
  }
}

// In component:
const [state, dispatch] = useReducer(calculatorReducer, initialState);
