body:
![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)

The `renderModalContent` function uses a long `if/else if` chain, which can be difficult to maintain and extend. A more declarative approach is to use a mapping object where keys correspond to the modal type and values are the components to render. This makes the code cleaner and adding new modal types simpler.

Example:
```typescript
const modalRenderers = {
  1: () => <PublicSubsidyModalContent {...data} />,
  2: () => <SelectContractModalContent {...data} />,
  // ... and so on
};

const renderModalContent = () => {
  if (activeModal === null) return null;
  const ModalContent = modalRenderers[activeModal];
  return ModalContent ? <ModalContent /> : null;
};
```

